By Splizard

Forum Post: http://minetest.net/forum/viewtopic.php?id=885

INSTALL:
----------
Minetest 0.4 and later:

Put the textures without subfolders in

<minetest directory>/textures/all/

So that you have them like so:

<minetest directory>/textures/all/default_grass.png
<minetest directory>/textures/all/fire_basic_flame.png

For installed Linux versions, <minetest directory> is ~/.minetest

Every Minetest version:

Put the textures without subfolders in any place you like, and add this configuration setting, with the proper path, in minetest.conf:

texture_path = C:\path\to\texture\directory

CHANGELOG:
------------
Version 1.0

    Initial release

Version 1.1

    Updated water, rails, torches, chests, glass, ladders and junglegrass

Version 1.2 

    Updated iron and coal

    Added mesecons, nature and secret_passage mod textures

    Added readme
    
Version 1.3

    Updated to latest minetest (deserts, doors, etc.)

    Added animated torches, particles, teleporter, snow mod textures.
    
    Updated all wood textures
    
    Removed lava texture

Version 1.4

    Updated bookshelf texture and added menu textures.

    Added locked sign, cotton, flowers, unified dyes, moreores, junglegrass mod textures.

UNINSTALL:
------------
Remove textures from <minetest directory>/textures/all/
or change your config.

